    <!-- Privacy Section -->
    <section id="about">
        <div id="header">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row" id="header">
                    <div class="col-lg-12">
                        <h2 class="section-heading text-center">About Us</h2>
                        <h3 class="section-subheading text-muted text-center"><em>“Twenty years from now you will be more disappointed by the things you didn’t do than by the ones you did do. So throw off the bowlines, sail away from the safe harbor. Catch the trade winds in your sails. Explore. Dream. Discover.”</em> - Mark Twain</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="explore">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-4 col-lg-offset-1">
                        <h2 class="section-title text-center">Explore</h2>
                        <h3 class="section-content">At VacayBug our vision is to create best travel experience for individuals by giving them access to holistic itineraries created by locals or likeminded people. Furthermore, we believe traditional itineraries are boring we want to allow our member to tell an unique story through their itineraries. After all, we like to think no two trips are the exactly the same</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="dream">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-4 col-lg-offset-7">
                        <h2 class="section-title text-center">Dream</h2>
                        <h3 class="section-content">VacayBug founders grow up from across the world - Taiwan, Mongolia and Cuba. They shared the same struggle when traveling - travel planning. They spend hours of research on the web and books to come up with the perfect itinerary but only to find out the perfect itinerary comes from family or friends who had been there. They decided to come together from LinkedIn, Facebook and Kifi, so they can come up with a way to revolutionaries travel planning</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="discover">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-4 col-lg-offset-1">
                        <h2 class="section-title text-center">Discover</h2>
                        <h3 class="section-content">Did you ever regret not visiting that perfect italian restaurant when you were in Rome, or a tuck-away viewpoint that oversees entire San Francisco? VacayBug wants you to travel like locals so you don’t miss out discovering places, and make sure you built your memories on the best a place can offer</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

